WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.860 --> 00:00:07.110
NEWSCASTER: We take you now to
Kermit the Frog with another

00:00:07.110 --> 00:00:08.620
fast breaking news story.

00:00:11.256 --> 00:00:13.340
[SIDE CONVERSATIONS]

00:00:13.340 --> 00:00:15.070
BOY: Where's my airplane?

00:00:15.070 --> 00:00:17.250
KERMIT: I think I got more like
the C minuses, you know?

00:00:17.250 --> 00:00:20.110
I was sort of a late bloomer.

00:00:20.110 --> 00:00:23.890
Oh, uh, hi ho, this is Kermit
the Frog of Sesame Street

00:00:23.890 --> 00:00:26.870
News, and I'm speaking to you
from inside a typical

00:00:26.870 --> 00:00:29.440
classroom on the first
day of school.

00:00:29.440 --> 00:00:31.970
And what an exciting day it is
for all of these students as

00:00:31.970 --> 00:00:34.810
they look forward to another
wonderful school year.

00:00:34.810 --> 00:00:36.890
Let's see if we can talk to
some of the happy students

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:38.690
before the teacher arrives.

00:00:38.690 --> 00:00:40.670
Excuse me?

00:00:40.670 --> 00:00:42.462
What's your name, please?

00:00:42.462 --> 00:00:44.270
COOKIE MONSTER: Cookie
Monster.

00:00:44.270 --> 00:00:44.885
KERMIT: Cookie Monster.

00:00:44.885 --> 00:00:45.200
Uh-huh.

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:48.290
And can you tell me,
how do you feel?

00:00:48.290 --> 00:00:51.470
What is going through your mind
on this wonderful first

00:00:51.470 --> 00:00:53.280
day of school?

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:55.660
COOKIE MONSTER: Me afraid.

00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:56.220
KERMIT: Afraid?

00:00:56.220 --> 00:00:56.725
COOKIE MONSTER: Yeah.

00:00:56.725 --> 00:00:58.720
KERMIT: What is there
to be afraid of?

00:00:58.720 --> 00:01:01.440
COOKIE MONSTER: Well, what
if teacher not like me?

00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:04.860
What if, what if me no
can find pencil?

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:08.246
What if me forgot where
bathroom was?

00:01:08.246 --> 00:01:09.280
Hm?

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:12.540
What if teacher not understand
me like cookies?

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:15.000
KERMIT: But you're supposed
to feel good about the

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:16.790
first day of school.

00:01:16.790 --> 00:01:18.480
COOKIE MONSTER: That
make it worse!

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:22.400
Me only want to feel this way.

00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.360
KERMIT: You know, come to
think of it, I remember

00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:27.010
feeling scared and nervous on
the first day of school.

00:01:27.010 --> 00:01:27.610
COOKIE MONSTER: Yeah?

00:01:27.610 --> 00:01:29.550
KERMIT: Any of the rest
of you feel that way?

00:01:29.550 --> 00:01:30.293
STUDENT: Yeah.

00:01:30.293 --> 00:01:31.562
STUDENT: Yeah.

00:01:31.562 --> 00:01:32.600
STUDENT: Really scared.

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:33.370
STUDENT: Yeah, I
feel that way.

00:01:33.370 --> 00:01:35.015
COOKIE MONSTER: Yeah?

00:01:35.015 --> 00:01:39.200
You mean, me not only one
who feels scared?

00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:39.845
KERMIT: No.

00:01:39.845 --> 00:01:40.340
STUDENT: No.

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:41.510
STUDENT: No, me too.

00:01:41.510 --> 00:01:43.880
COOKIE MONSTER: Oh, me
feel so much better.

00:01:43.880 --> 00:01:45.720
Thank you.

00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:46.150
KERMIT: Oh, look.

00:01:46.150 --> 00:01:47.270
Here comes your teacher now.

00:01:47.270 --> 00:01:50.480
COOKIE MONSTER: Oh, oh, oh!

00:01:50.480 --> 00:01:52.230
You know what?

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:53.860
He not look scary.

00:01:53.860 --> 00:01:54.340
KERMIT: No.

00:01:54.340 --> 00:01:54.690
See there?

00:01:54.690 --> 00:01:55.900
There's nothing to
be scared of.

00:01:55.900 --> 00:01:58.610
I'm sure he'll understand
if you forget things.

00:01:58.610 --> 00:01:59.820
COOKIE MONSTER: Even
the cookies?

00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:00.160
KERMIT: Mm-hm.

00:02:00.160 --> 00:02:00.660
Even the cookies.

00:02:00.660 --> 00:02:01.580
COOKIE MONSTER: OK.

00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:02.250
MR. MORLEY: Hello, everyone.

00:02:02.250 --> 00:02:02.860
I'm Mr. Morley.

00:02:02.860 --> 00:02:07.020
Mr. be your teacher this year.

00:02:07.020 --> 00:02:09.080
KERMIT: I'll just tip-toe out.

00:02:09.080 --> 00:02:11.880
MR. MORLEY: Young frog,
what's your name?

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:13.820
KERMIT: Uh, Kermit
the Frog, sir.

00:02:13.820 --> 00:02:15.040
Sesame Street News.

00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:17.125
MR. MORLEY: Kermit, would you
take your seat, please?

00:02:17.125 --> 00:02:19.800
KERMIT: Uh, but I'm afraid,
see, you don't understand.

00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:20.910
MR. MORLEY: I understand.

00:02:20.910 --> 00:02:24.650
A lot of you are afraid on the
first day of school, but

00:02:24.650 --> 00:02:26.195
that's no reason to leave.

00:02:28.710 --> 00:02:32.850
Now I'm going to show
you your new books.

00:02:32.850 --> 00:02:35.010
KERMIT: This is Kermit the Frog
returning you to your

00:02:35.010 --> 00:02:36.700
regularly scheduled program.

00:02:36.700 --> 00:02:39.620
MR. MORLEY: Now Kermit, you
can't talk and listen at the

00:02:39.620 --> 00:02:41.910
same time, can you?

00:02:41.910 --> 00:02:43.790
KERMIT: No, sir.

00:02:43.790 --> 00:02:45.040
COOKIE MONSTER: Shh.

